Title : Portal:Current events/2014 April 28
Text : <!-- All news items below this line -->{{Current events header|2014|04|28}}

;Armed conflicts and attacks
*[[Post-coup unrest in Egypt (2013–14)|Post-coup unrest in Egypt]]:
**An [[Egypt]]ian court hands down a death sentence on 638 [[Muslim Brotherhood]] supporters, among them the group's top leader [[Mohamed Badie]]. [http://uk.reuters.com/article/2014/04/28/uk-egypt-brotherhood-idUKKBN0DE0LK20140428 (Reuters)]
*[[2014 pro-Russian unrest in Ukraine]]:
**Pro-Russian gunmen seize the town of [[Kostyantynivka]], the latest in a string of towns in the eastern [[Ukraine]]. [http://post.us/2014/04/28/pro-russia-gunmen-seize-another-east-ukraine-town-afp/ (AFP via Post)]
**The [[United States]] imposes a third round of sanctions against [[Russia]], reportedly in response to Russia encouraging rebellion in [[eastern Ukraine]].  [https://www.reuters.com/article/2014/04/28/us-ukraine-crisis-idUSBREA3O16720140428 (Reuters)]
**The mayor of the [[Eastern Ukraine|eastern Ukrainian]] city of [[Kharkiv]], [[Gennady Kernes]], is shot in the back by an unknown assailant.  [http://www.cnn.com/2014/04/28/world/europe/ukraine-crisis/ (BBC)]
**Two thousand people holding a peaceful demonstration in Donetsk for a united Ukraine are attacked with bats and teargas by pro-Russians. [http://www.nbcnews.com/storyline/ukraine-crisis/pro-ukraine-demonstration-donetsk-turns-violent-n91656 (NBC)]
*[[Iraqi insurgency (post-U.S. withdrawal)]]:
**[[Suicide bomb]] attacks kill dozens of people at a political rally and at early polling places for the [[Iraqi parliamentary election, 2014|election]] to be held on April 30. [http://www.abc.net.au/news/2014-04-29/dozens-killed-in-suicide-bomb-attacks-ahead-of-iraq-election/5417006 (Reuters via ABC News Australia)]

;Arts and culture
*More than 50 royal [[mummies]] have been discovered by Egyptian and [[Switzerland|Swiss]] archeologists in the newly opened [[KV40]] tomb in Egypt's Valley of the Kings. [http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2014/05/140501-mummy-royal-tut-discovery-egypt-science/ (National Geographic News)]
*[[Scottish-American]] comedian [[Craig Ferguson]] announces his departure from the [[CBS]] late-night talk show ''[[The Late Late Show with Craig Ferguson|The Late Late Show]]'', effective December 2014. [https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2014/04/28/craig-ferguson-will-leave-cbs-late-late-show/8436401/ (''USA Today'')]

;Business and economics
*[[Microsoft]] announces a major vulnerability in [[Internet Explorer]] versions 6 to 11 that could enable hackers to gain access and user rights to its customers' computers. [https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-27184188 (BBC)]

;Disasters and accidents
*[[Malaysia Airlines Flight 370]]:
**The search area for the missing aircraft in the southern [[Indian Ocean]] is expanded with any debris likely to be found on the ocean floor with the minimum time anticipated for the search eight months. [http://tvnz.co.nz/world-news/mh370-search-area-expanded-5942662 (TV New Zealand)]
*[[Tornado outbreak of April 27–30, 2014]]:
**Seventeen people are killed by [[tornado]]es after a huge storm system sweeps across the [[Central United States|central]] and [[southern United States]].  [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-27183974 (BBC)]

;International relations
*[[Slovakia]] and [[Ukraine]] agree to a deal that will allow gas from [[Central Europe]] to reach Ukraine via Slovakia. [https://www.bbc.com/news/business-27177763 (BBC)]

;Law and crime
*[[United States House of Representatives|U.S. Representative]] [[Michael Grimm (politician)|Michael Grimm]] is taken into federal custody on charges relating to a failed restaurant business and allegations that he made false statements.  [http://www.cnn.com/2014/04/28/politics/congress-grimm/index.html?hpt=hp_t2 (CNN)]
*[[Paul Simon]] and wife [[Edie Brickell]] are arrested and charged with disorderly conduct.  [https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-27194863 (BBC)]

;Politics and elections
*An Egyptian court bans the [[April 6 Youth Movement]] over claims of espionage and of "damaging the image of the state". [http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/1/64/99998/Egypt/Politics-/BREAKING-Egypt-court-bans-April--over-espionage-cl.aspx (''Al-Ahram'')] [http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/sns-rt-us-egypt-brotherhood-april6-20140428,0,7459703.story (''Chicago Tribune'')]

